17/06/2010
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The anti-terrorism unit of the Kosovo Police on Thursday (June 17th) arrested a Kosovo Albanian wanted by the United States on terrorism charges, EULEX announced. 
The arrest, in the divided town of Mitrovica, followed an extradition request from the US. 
Police also raided a house as part of the operation. 
A US attorney for the District of North Carolina has charged the man with providing support to terrorists and conspiracy to kill, kidnap and damage property in a foreign country. 
His name has not been released. 
(RTS, DPA, Telegrafi - 17/06/10)
